Date: Tue, 27 Jan 2026 00:09:15 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Improve Share Extension file handling

### Motivation
- Make the Share Extension more reliable when copying shared items so temporary provider URLs don't expire before the extension persists them.
- Avoid race conditions while loading multiple attachments concurrently from `NSItemProvider`.
- Ensure security-scoped URLs are handled when copying files into the App Group so the host app can read them after handoff.

### Description
- Add thread-safety to attachment collection by protecting the `collectedUrls` array with an `NSLock` in `ShareViewController.swift`.
- Prefer `loadFileRepresentation` and copy file representations into a stable temporary location via a new `copyToTemporaryLocation` helper, and fall back to `loadItem`/data when needed, inside `ShareViewController.swift`.
- Handle security-scoped resources when copying both into the temporary location and into the App Group by calling `startAccessingSecurityScopedResource()` / `stopAccessingSecurityScopedResource()` in `copyToTemporaryLocation` and `copyToSharedContainer`.
- Keep the existing handoff flow that writes a `shared_media.json` manifest into the App Group and opens the host app with `ShareMedia://shared`; the extension manifests and entitlements (`Info.plist`, `ShareExtension.entitlements`) remain part of the extension configuration.

### Testing
- No automated tests were run for this change.
